6:
I don't suppose she's living a happy
life... How could she, after what I did?
14:
The look on your face tells me
whatever it is, it ain't sunshine and
rainbows.
17:
A certain synthetic. She was
programmed to serve me, but I let
her go.
20:
I thought I would never know
freedom, so I released her from my
service in the hopes that she would
live the life I couldn't.
21:
But she wasn't given any tools to be
successful outside of her role. I
abandoned her to an unknown fate.
23: Didn't she object or say anything?
27:
I didn't give her a chance to think or
formulate a response.
31:
Is this your first time searching for
her?
33:
No. I came a few times with Bulleta
before leaving for Starview Village.
34:
But we never found her. Maybe
she's...
38:
She could be dead. Or suffering a
fate worse than death.
41:
Or she might be here somewhere,
hating me for abandoning her. She
might be sharpening her rage into a
blade that will pierce me some day.
42:
The thing that scares me the most is
the idea of my happiness shattering
because I stole someone else's.
45:
Are you disgusted with me? Do you
think someone as selfish as me
doesn't deserve to be in Starview
Village?
48:
Of course you do. I'm not altruistic;
I'm as self-centered as they come...
It's no surprise that you would hate
me.
55:
First of all, how's deciding that I hate
you any different from deciding you
know what'd make that synthetic
friend of yours happy?
58:
She could be living it up somewhere,
having the time of her life.
62:
Are you saying I did the right thing
for her?
65:
Heck if I know. That's for the two of
you to decide.
69:
Thanks, Nimbus. You know exactly
what to say to cheer me up.
73:
We should be getting back. There's
still so much we need to do before
the trading post opens.
82:
You're doing good! Just a few more
steps and you're there! Take 'em
nice and easy, okay?
86:
And if you need help, we're right
here!
110:
Mm, it's so delicious, even without
flavor enhancers.
114:
Nothing beats ice cold water after
exercise, huh?
117:
You've come real far. Pretty soon
you'll be walking on your own.
120:
Of course. I'll be giving Bulleta a run
for her money in no time.
125:
Uh, maybe we should set more
realistic goals?
129:
Someday I'm going to be a proper
lady who can stand strong on her
own.
131:
I want to stand by the people who
mean the most to me and look out
for them, as they've looked out for
me. My journey of self-improvement
has only begun.
135: If anyone can succeed, Love, it's you.
137:
Thank you. I think so too. But, you
know... Sometimes I get stuck in my
own head.
140:
If you could snap me out of it when I
start to get blue again, I'd
appreciate it. You don't mind, do you?
149:
You don't have to ask permission for
every little thing. You're not a little
kid.
154:
Hey! You could be nicer! Bulleta
would never do that to me!
158:
Heh, I thought you said you wanted
to be a proper lady who stands on
her own two feet. I'm not about to
coddle you.
163:
I'll walk tall until my journey ends. No,
even after, when I'm all grown up.
167:
I can't wait to see you again, Bulleta!
The next time you see me, I'll be
someone you can proudly call your
partner!
